      "text": [
        " الْكُفْوُ أَنْ يَكُونَ عَفِيفاً وَ عِنْدَهُ يَسَارٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al hakam, from Aban, from a man, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The match is that he happens to be chaste, and with him is wealth’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Aban from a man who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Proper match is one who is chaste and affluent.’” "
        ]
      }
